rebuke /rɪˈbjuːk/

(rebuking,rebuked,rebukes) 

1. V-T If you rebuke someone, you speak severely to them because they have said or done something that you do not approve of. 谴责 [正式] 

例： The president rebuked the House and Senate for not passing those bills within 100 days. 总统谴责参众两院未在100天内通过那些法案。 

2. N-VAR Rebuke is also a noun. 谴责 

例： His statements drew a stinging rebuke from the chairman. 他的申明受到了主席严厉的谴责。

